# Contains Duplicate

## Difficulty
Easy

## Approach
Use a hash set to store the elements that have already been seen. Traverse the array and check whether the current element is present in the set. If it is, a duplicate has been found, so return `True`. Otherwise, add the element to the set and continue. If the traversal completes without finding any duplicate, return `False`.

## Complexity
- **Time Complexity:** O(n)
- **Space Complexity:** O(n)

## Code
```python
class Solution:
    def containsDuplicate(self, nums):
        seen = set()

        for i in nums:
            if i in seen:
                return True
            seen.add(i)

        return False
```
